TITLE: Pfizer's Omicron-Targeting Covid-19 Vaccines Generate Stronger Immune Response
SUMMARY: One shot that was tested targeted Omicron specifically, while another was modified to work against the strain and the original virus.

TITLE: After Roe v. Wade Ruling, Employers Weigh In on Abortion and Benefits---Cautiously
SUMMARY: Businesses with health plans covering abortion now are weighing whether and how to pay for employees to travel to a state where the procedure is legal.

TITLE: Appeals Court Delays FDA's Ban on Juul E-Cigarettes
SUMMARY: Vaping company sought relief from FDA ban and has consulted with restructuring lawyers on possible bankruptcy filing.

TITLE: What It Takes to Buy Your First Home Now
SUMMARY: Interest rates are rising, supply is thin and bidding wars remain widespread. “It’s just so ridiculous and disheartening.”

TITLE: Spirit Airlines Sticks With Frontier Deal After Sweetened Offer
SUMMARY: Frontier puts up extra $2 per share to fend off competing bid from JetBlue; Spirit shareholders set to vote on Frontier deal June 30.

TITLE: The Strange Art of Asking People How Much Inflation They Expect
SUMMARY: Consumers’ replies show a fondness for round numbers and partisanship, and can sway the Fed’s interest-rate decisions.

TITLE: Consumer Sentiment at Record Low Is Another Ominous Economic Sign
SUMMARY: Consumer sentiment fell to its lowest point on record, reflecting that elevated inflation weighs on Americans’ moods and adding to indicators of a slowdown in the world’s largest economy.

TITLE: The Controversial Economics of Abortion Law
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court’s decision overturning Roe v. Wade will bring new scrutiny to research over the past several decades studying the socioeconomic effects of abortion liberalization.

TITLE: Student-Loan Forgiveness for Public-Service Workers Reaches $8.1 Billion
SUMMARY: The tally since October stems from the Biden administration’s overhaul of a largely moribund student debt forgiveness program for public-service employees.

TITLE: Europe's Workers Brace for Tough Times as Real Wages Fall
SUMMARY: Europeans are likely to see their spending power fall faster than their U.S. counterparts, as Russia’s invasion of Ukraine sends inflation on a fresh surge, threatening to push the continent into recession.

TITLE: Amazon's Chinese-Seller Problem
SUMMARY: Jeff Bezos wanted to build the ‘everything store’—and now the company is drowning in China-based sellers hawking the same items under a dizzying array of brands

TITLE: Investor Ron Gonen Thinks a Greener Economy Depends on Businesses
SUMMARY: The CEO of Closed Loop Partners aims to make a profit by reducing landfill waste.

TITLE: EY Grapples With Partner Pay, Bear Market in Breakup
SUMMARY: The Big Four accounting firm has made changes to its earlier plan to split the company, including agreeing to offer payout to partners who retire this year or next.

TITLE: Lawmakers Want FTC to Investigate Apple, Google Over Mobile Tracking
SUMMARY: Identifiers built into iOS and Android facilitate the collection and sale of personal data, four Democrats said in a letter to the Federal Trade Commission.

TITLE: Theranos Ex-President's Case Goes to Jury
SUMMARY: Deliberations began over whether the blood-testing startup executive Ramesh “Sunny” Balwani lied to investors and patients.

TITLE: Chevron to Cut Back in California, Remain Based in State
SUMMARY: The oil company intends to sell its current global headquarters, and it offers to move some workers to Texas.
